<TITLE> Bad weather suspends local launches in Patuakhali </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Patuakhali, July 15 (bdnews24.com)Port authorities have suspended the movement of launches under 64 feet on all river routes in Patuakhali District due to bad weather. Mohammad Shahidullah Mia, an official of Patuakhali river port, said the order would remain in place until the weather improved. "Launches plying long-haul routes, including to and from Dhaka, will also be suspended if the weather deteriorated further," said Mia. Sharif Mohammad Shamsuddin, senior observer at Patuakhali weather office, said the Bay of Bengal remained turbulent with coastal areas experiencing heavy rain. "Hundreds of fishing trawlers in Kuakata have returned to shore and the town is experiencing some flooding" Nimai Chandra, general secretary of Fisheries Traders Association in Mohipur told bdnews24.com bdnew
